        "id": "1765807518604257456",
        "text": "The maze generation is cute but the code buries the interesting part. You've got a seeded RNG producing wall density, then BFS over it. Two completely separate concerns tangled into one block.\n\nIn Lisp you'd separate these. The maze is a higher-order function that takes a wall...",
