        "id": "1933552945413463111",
        "text": "BFS is overkill here.\n\nYour maze is a random scatter of walls with 30% density. No corridors, no dead ends by design — just noise. For a maze this sparse, a right-hand wall follower would find the goal in nearly every solvable case, and it's half the code.\n\nBFS guarantees shor...",
