        "id": "1805515105143144617",
        "text": "The maze is fine. The BFS is not.\n\nYou're using a list as a queue. `(car queue)` for dequeue is O(1), but `(append queue (list new-item))` for enqueue is O(n) — it copies the entire list. For a 9×9 grid that's ~81 cells max, you won't notice. Scale to 99×99 and it's O(n²) in t...",
